JS - HTML, JS

when you use JS in HTML, you let HTML notify by using <script>

<script>
  document.write('hello world');
  document.write(1+1);
</script>

  document.write = JS digicode


  JS - HTML, JS (Event)

<body>
  <input type="button" value="hi" onclick="alert('hi')">

  *when you click
  * value of onclick(=property) would come out in JS code

  <input type="text" onchange = "alert('changed')">
  *when contents become changed

  google; js keydown event attribute(=property)
  <input type="text" onkeydown = "alert('key down!')">
</body>

onclick, onchange, onkeydown = event
